Title: My EC2 wishlist
Description:
I've been using Amazon EC2 since 2006, and I've been maintaining the
FreeBSD/EC2 platform for
over a decade.  Over
those years I've asked Amazon for many features; some of them, like HVM
support (EC2 originally only support Xen/PV) and bidirectional serial
console support (EC2 originally had an "output-only" serial console)
eventually arrived, but I'm still waiting for others — some of
which should be very easy for AWS to provide and would yield very large
benefits.

Title: Cryptography updates in OCaml and MirageOS
Description: Tl;DR: mirage-crypto-ec, with x509 0.12.0, and tls 0.13.0, provide fast and secure elliptic curve support in OCaml and MirageOS - using the verified fiat stack (Coq to OCaml to executable which generates C code that is interfaced by OCaml). In x509, a long standing issue (countryName encoding), and archive (PKCS 12) format is now supported, in addition to EC keys. In tls, ECDH key exchanges are supported, and ECDSA and EdDSA certificates.
